To create a colorful and interactive website based on the mock-up, you can use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Here's a basic example:

HTML:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Joke Website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>My Joke Website</h1>
        <div class="joke-box">
            <div class="joke-type">
                <input type="radio" id="funny-joke" name="joke-type" value="funny" checked>
                <label for="funny-joke">Funny Joke</label>
            </div>
            <div class="joke-type">
                <input type="radio" id="reveal-punchline" name="joke-type" value="reveal-punchline">
                <label for="reveal-punchline">Push to Reveal Punchline?</label>
            </div>
            <div id="joke-content" class="hidden">
                <p id="joke-text">Enter your joke here!</p>
                <button id="submit-joke">Submit Joke</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
CSS:
```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background-color: #f2f2f2;
}

.container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px;
    background-color: #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

.joke-box {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: space-between;
}

.joke-type input[type="radio"] {
    margin-right: 10px;
}

.joke-type label {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 5px;
}

.joke-content {
    display: none;
    margin-top: 20px;
}

#submit-joke {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
}

#submit-joke:hover {
    background-color: #45a049;
}
```
JavaScript:
```javascript
const jokeInput = document.getElementById("joke-text");
const submitButton = document.getElementById("submit-joke");

submitButton.addEventListener("click", function () {
    if (jokeInput.value.trim() !== "") {
        alert("You entered: " + jokeInput.value);
    } else {
        alert("Please enter a joke!");
    }
});
```
This example creates a simple joke website with a container, joke types, and a joke submission button. When the user clicks the "Submit Joke" button, an alert will display the entered joke or a message if the input is empty.
